                                 Core Concepts of Spring
                                 ------------------------
1) IOC(Inversion of Control)
      IOC means the control of creating and managing objects is given to spring container instead of developer.
      Without IOC - We create object using "new"
      with IOC - Spring creates and manages objects for us.
   Control of creating obejcts is invered(control tranferred from us to spring container)
   IOC is concept - IOC tells who controls obejcts.

2) Dependency(object) Injection:
     DI is the process of providing required depenedncies(obejcts) to the class by spring.
     -> Instead of creating dependencies inside a class they are injected from outside.

Without DI:
    class Engine{}
    
    class Car{
        Engine engine = new Engine();
    }

With DI  
    @Componenet
    class Engine{}
    
    @Component
    class Car{
        @Autowired
        Engine engine;
    }
